'''Al-Qasim al-Ma'mun ibn Hammud''' was an [[Arab]] [[Caliph]] of [[Caliphate of Córdoba|Córdoba]] in [[Muslim Spain]] for two periods, 1018 to 1021, and again for a short time in 1023.

This was during a short period when the caliphate was held by the [[Hammudid dynasty]].

