The '''Apurinã''', also called '''TheIpurinã, Ipurinãn, Kangite, Popengare''' ([[endonym]]), are an [[Indigenous peoples in Brazil|indigenous people]] who live near the [[Purus River]] in western [[Brazil]] and speak [[Apurinã language|Apurinã]].

