'''Lubu''' people are an ethnic group who live in central [[Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]]. They are similar to the [[Kubu people]], and are also ancestral to the '''Siladang''' people.<ref name =medanbisnisdaily >[http://medanbisnisdaily.com/m/news/arsip/read/2011/01/18/15636/melirik-kehidupan-warga-siladang/ ''MELIRIK KEHIDUPAN WARGA SILADANG'' MEDAN BISNIS DAILY] </ref> They live in the mountainous regions of Padang, Lawas, Ankola, and Mandheling of southern Batakland.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N3ILAAAAIAAJ |title= Sumatra: its History and People |series=Wiener Beiträge zur Kulturgeschichte und Linguistik, Volume 3 |publisher=Verlag F. Berger & Söhne|date= 1935 |author=Edwin M. Loeb |pages=295&ndash;297 }}</ref> They are now in the process of being absorbed by the [[Batak]]. In the early 20th century, they were a migratory people who lived in tree houses, and now are still a tribal people. Although they live near the rivers, they are fearful of water.<ref name="joshua">{{cite web |url = https://joshuaproject.net/people_groups/13136/ID |title = Lubu in Indonesia |publisher = joshua project}}</ref>  They speak the [[Lubu language]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZnvGBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA15#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Critical Survey Of Studies On The Languages of Sumatra |author= P. Voorhoeve |page=15 |publisher=Springer|year=1955 |isbn=9789401505222 }}</ref>
